Package gov.nih.nlm.ling.composition

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ArgumentIdentification
    This class contains static methods to process a DocumentGraph recursively to identify arguments of predicates and create a SemanticGraph object that contains the full semantics of the Document.
    ArgumentPropagation
    A class that includes static methods that determine whether and how to propagate semantic objects that appear further down the embedding graph (and not as immediate children) as arguments for a given predicate.
    ArgumentRule
    Represents a rule that is used to identify the argument of a Predicate.
    DependencyClass
    Represents a higher-level classification of dependencies.
    EmbeddingCategorization
    A static graph representation of the embedding categorization.
    ScalarModalityValueComposition
    A class that includes static methods for scalar modality value composition.
    SourcePropagation
    This class contains a static method to propagate source values of predications.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    ScalarModalityValueComposition.ScaleShift
